(---) Tj
T* (name: study-guide-compiler) Tj
T* (description: Automates the repetitive task of parsing, cleaning, and structuring unstructured) Tj
T* (text files, assignment sheets, and raw programming source code snippets into streamlined,) Tj
T* (beginner-friendly Markdown study guides for peer tutoring. Trigger phrases: "Compile my) Tj
T* (raw notes and code snippets into a structured peer study guide." "Run the automation to) Tj
T* (filter out compiler logs and format these programming guidelines." "Turn this messy) Tj
T* (assignment documentation into a clean, simplified reference sheet.") Tj
T* (---) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (# Instructions) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Accept and Validate Inputs: Gather all connected source materials, including raw text) Tj
T* (notes, assignment outlines, and specific code blocks \(such as C++ class definitions\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. Filter and Remove Noise: Parse the documentation to scrub out system logs, redundant) Tj
T* (compiler warnings, and distracting formatting artifacts.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. Structure the Core Concepts: Group the remaining information into clean, logical) Tj
T* (modules based on topic headings and core operational rules.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (4. Simplify Technical Terminology: Translate complex code logic and abstract theories into) Tj
T* (highly accessible, beginner-friendly explanations suitable for peer tutoring.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5. Format the Output: Compile the processed material into a clean Markdown document) Tj
T* (utilizing clear headers, concise bullet points, and distinct syntax-highlighted code blocks.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (6. Perform a Quality Check: Review the finalized guide to verify that no critical functional) Tj
T* (logic was lost during simplification and ensure the tone remains highly readable before) Tj
T* (outputting.) Tj
ET
endstream
